#7 bad order intrans. This is an alternative word order used for intransitive sentences which may be valid. I don't see it that often, and when I do mostly with pronouns. I'll have to dig through the literature a little more.

Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
biryekomo niratano 
biryekomo ni-rata-no 
boy SIII-weep-IMM.PAST
`?The boy wept.'

#7 agreement ## All of the examples with pronouns, except for amna (which I didn't do for reasons I talked about in my writeup), need to be deleted. I think they're grammatical, but they're not natural and don't appear in the examples.  ## None of these examples have collective versions because that's encoded onto the tense, agreement suffix, which we haven't done yet.

Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {agreement}
kiewehno uro 
ki-eweh-no uro 
SI-take_bath-IMM.PAST 1sg 
`I took a bath'

